										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<h1 class="has-text-align-center"><strong>7 of The Best Win Back Email Examples We’ve Seen</strong></h1>
<div class="post-content-category"><a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/category/email-marketing" rel="category tag">Email Marketing</a></div>


<figure class="wp-block-image alignwide size-large"><img width="1024" height="437" src="http://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Win-Back-Email-Examples-WordPress-1024x437.jpg" alt="Win Back Email Examples WordPress" class="wp-image-117910" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Win-Back-Email-Examples-WordPress-1024x437.jpg 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Win-Back-Email-Examples-WordPress-300x128.jpg 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Win-Back-Email-Examples-WordPress-768x328.jpg 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Win-Back-Email-Examples-WordPress-1536x656.jpg 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Win-Back-Email-Examples-WordPress-2048x875.jpg 2048w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Win-Back-Email-Examples-WordPress-380x162.jpg 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Win-Back-Email-Examples-WordPress-600x256.jpg 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Win-Back-Email-Examples-WordPress-760x325.jpg 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Win-Back-Email-Examples-WordPress-1440x615.jpg 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Win-Back-Email-Examples-WordPress-960x410.jpg 960w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Win-Back-Email-Examples-WordPress-82x35.jpg 82w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Win-Back-Email-Examples-WordPress-117x50.jpg 117w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Win-Back-Email-Examples-WordPress-740x316.jpg 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Win-Back-Email-Examples-WordPress-220x94.jpg 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Win-Back-Email-Examples-WordPress-385x164.jpg 385w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>


<div id="preamble-block_603f828999ef3" class="block-preamble"><p>What is one thing that makes a marketer’s heart sink perhaps more than any other?</p>
</div>






<p>Seeing your emails, with their specially crafted copy and hand-picked subject lines, lying unopened in your subscribers’ inboxes.</p>



<p>Falling open rates and rising to unsubscribe rates are disheartening and worry-inducing and can occur for many different reasons, from subscribers being unimpressed with your product range&nbsp;or prices&nbsp;to emails simply not standing out enough from the inbox crowd.</p>



<p>But all is not lost. In fact, they are signs that it’s time to use your secret weapon: win-back emails. Win-back emails are designed specially to re-engage inactive subscribers in a number of ways. And they work:&nbsp;<a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://marketingland.com/email-win-back-programs-work-81574&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1614777976770000&amp;usg=AOvVaw2dHoX6X_uFajKkD0EP1RpW" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">45 percent of subscribers</a>&nbsp;who receive a win-back email will go on to open future emails from you.</p>



<p>Why not simply invest in new customers instead? Surely they’ll be easier to convince? Well, it turns out that the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.invespcro.com/blog/customer-acquisition-retention/&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1614777976771000&amp;usg=AOvVaw3aND0LKHLd9xv-oWWw4mvF" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">probability that an existing customer will make a purchase from you</a>&nbsp;is around 60–70 percent, while the likelihood of selling to a new prospect is only around 5–20 percent. You do the math.</p>



<p>There are so many ways to approach a win back email, so here are seven examples of emails from brands winning back their subscribers left, right and center. I’ve taken the liberty of pointing out exactly what each one did right, so you can build a successful win back campaign for your brand.</p>


<div id="contentupgrade-block_5e6f406d8dc96" class="block-content-upgrade">
