<h2 id="h.ez7aic2keijx"><strong>Conclusion</strong></h2>



<p>At the end of the day, a well-crafted automotive email has five main components:</p>



<ol><li>Eye-catching visuals</li><li>Concise copy that conveys essential information without rattling on</li><li>An easy to digest layout</li><li>Clear, logically placed CTAs to get readers where you need them to go</li><li>Cohesive branding elements</li></ol>



<p>As long as your content checks all of those boxes, you should be in good shape. Remember that&nbsp;<a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/email-marketing-stats?__hstc%3D200701681.3d4dd279ed7cf78785c07bae03db7d11.1612292304949.1612465700853.1613147872411.4%26__hssc%3D200701681.3.1613147872411%26__hsfp%3D2010596167&amp;sa=D&amp;source=editors&amp;ust=1613566518307000&amp;usg=AOvVaw1EbJ-eJnRrs7qZXhHB4PYz" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">nearly half of readers</a>&nbsp;now open their email on mobile. So you’ll always want to keep the mobile viewing experience in mind.</p>



<p>The automotive email examples listed here all go above and beyond. It should provide you with plenty of creative fuel for your own email campaign.</p>



<p><em>Which of these examples stood out the most to you?</em></p>
