</div>


<h2><strong>Table of Contents</strong></h2>



<p><a href="#1">1. The Amazing Benefits of Permission-Based Emails Marketing </a></p>



<p><a href="#2">2. Higher Email Open Rate</a></p>



<p><a href="#3">3. Increase Conversions</a></p>



<p><a href="#4">4. Better Sender Score</a></p>



<p><a href="#5">5. Strong Brand Reputation</a></p>



<p><a href="#6">6. Larger ROI</a></p>



<p><a href="#7">7. Examples of Brands That Have Completely Nailed Permission-Based Emails Marketing</a></p>



<h2 id="1"><strong>The Amazing Benefits of Permission-Based Emails Marketing&nbsp;</strong></h2>



<p>Only sending email to readers after they’ve given their consent is a win-win. Why? It ensures readers receive content they’re genuinely interested in and prevents any “feather-ruffling” on their end.&nbsp;</p>



<p>We all know how annoying it is to receive unsolicited emails from companies you’ve never heard of. It’s the modern equivalent of a sleazy door-to-door salesman or telemarketer, and seldom does it lead to positive results.&nbsp;</p>



<p>At best, unsolicited emails are quickly glossed over and forgotten. At worst, they greatly irk a reader, dissolve your brand reputation, and are added to spam lists.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The EU’s GDPR has even taken steps to battle unwanted solicitation like this, and it could lead to fines and penalties at some point. It’s just not a good way to do business, and it’s something that can not only create a rift between you and your audience but a massive chasm.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Permission-based email marketing, however, is a much better approach, with <a href="https://www.salesforce.com/blog/email-marketing-stats-blog/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">77 percent</a> of consumers saying they prefer this technique.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="768" height="432" src="http://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image7-3.png" alt="Permission-Based Email Marketing" class="wp-image-115913" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image7-3.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image7-3-300x169.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image7-3-380x214.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image7-3-600x338.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image7-3-760x428.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image7-3-62x35.png 62w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image7-3-89x50.png 89w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image7-3-740x416.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image7-3-220x124.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image7-3-385x217.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px" /></figure>



<p>And as for your brand, there are a ton of benefits, including the following.&nbsp;</p>



<h2 id="2"><strong>Higher Email Open Rate</strong></h2>



<p>Let’s start at the top. Permission-based emails are far more likely to be opened than non-permission-based emails.&nbsp;</p>



<p>“Research shows that the average open rates for email campaigns to recipients who have given you permission to email them is <a href="https://www.campaignmonitor.com/resources/guides/permission/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">around 30–40 percent.</a>”</p>



<p>The average open rate for non-permission-based emails? A measly 2 percent. Put yourself in the shoes of a reader for a second. Which email would you be more likely to open—a highly relevant, ultra-targeted email from a brand that you subscribed to, know, and trust?&nbsp;</p>



<p>Take this email from <a href="https://www.ray-ban.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Ray-Ban</a>, for example. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="1024" height="29" src="http://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image11-3-1024x29.png" alt="Permission-Based Email Marketing" class="wp-image-115917" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image11-3-1024x29.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image11-3-300x9.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image11-3-768x22.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image11-3-1536x44.png 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image11-3-380x11.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image11-3-600x17.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image11-3-760x22.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image11-3-1440x41.png 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image11-3-180x5.png 180w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image11-3-250x7.png 250w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image11-3-740x21.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image11-3-220x6.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image11-3-385x11.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image11-3.png 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>Or, a sketchy, spammy, completely irrelevant email from a brand you’ve never heard of and certainly never subscribed to, like this?</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="1024" height="34" src="http://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image19-3-1024x34.png" alt="Permission-Based Email Marketing" class="wp-image-115925" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image19-3-1024x34.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image19-3-300x10.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image19-3-768x25.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image19-3-1536x51.png 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image19-3-380x13.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image19-3-600x20.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image19-3-760x25.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image19-3-1440x48.png 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image19-3-180x6.png 180w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image19-3-250x8.png 250w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image19-3-740x25.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image19-3-220x7.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image19-3-385x13.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image19-3.png 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>The first one, obviously.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Permission-based email marketing instantly cranks up your open rate, which is the first step in getting readers to check out your offer.&nbsp;</p>



<h2 id="3"><strong>Increased Conversions</strong></h2>



<p>Needless to say, sending emails to people who actually want to receive them will lead to more click-throughs, and inevitably more conversions. It’s hard to get readers to even open unsolicited emails, much less get them to engage and buy.&nbsp;</p>



<p>But strictly sending emails to readers who have expressed a clear interest in your brand massively increases the chances of them making a purchase.&nbsp;</p>



<p>According to data from Campaign Monitor, the average click-through rate when you have permission is about <a href="https://www.campaignmonitor.com/resources/guides/permission/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">20 percent</a>, whereas it’s only 0.2 percent when you don’t have permission. </p>



<p>The numbers speak for themselves and really put the disparity in conversions into perspective. And here’s the thing. Once someone buys from you initially, they’re more likely to do it again and are more receptive to future emails.&nbsp;</p>



<p>In fact, Michael Brenner of Marketing Insider Group writes that “<a href="https://marketinginsidergroup.com/content-marketing/email-marketing-conversion-rate-comparison/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">almost half (46.1 percent) of email recipients</a> open emails that are related to their purchase.”</p>



<p>Take this <a href="https://reallygoodemails.com/emails/how-did-you-sleep" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">post-purchase email from Casper Sleep</a>, for example. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="921" height="1024" src="http://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image13-3-921x1024.png" alt="Permission-Based Email Marketing" class="wp-image-115919" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image13-3-921x1024.png 921w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image13-3-270x300.png 270w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image13-3-768x854.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image13-3-380x422.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image13-3-600x667.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image13-3-760x845.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image13-3-31x35.png 31w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image13-3-45x50.png 45w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image13-3-441x490.png 441w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image13-3-220x245.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image13-3-385x428.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image13-3.png 1110w" sizes="(max-width: 921px) 100vw, 921px" /></figure>



<p>It sets the stage for further engagement and additional purchases. That’s why getting permission is so crucial in the long run.&nbsp;</p>



<h2 id="4"><strong>Better Sender Score</strong></h2>



<p>Spam is a huge problem, and it accounts for an astonishing <a href="https://www.propellercrm.com/blog/email-spam-statistics" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">45 percent</a> of email content.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="780" height="528" src="http://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image8-3.png" alt="Permission-Based Email Marketing" class="wp-image-115914" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image8-3.png 780w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image8-3-300x203.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image8-3-768x520.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image8-3-380x257.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image8-3-600x406.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image8-3-760x514.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image8-3-52x35.png 52w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image8-3-74x50.png 74w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image8-3-724x490.png 724w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image8-3-220x149.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image8-3-385x261.png 385w" sizes="(max-width: 780px) 100vw, 780px" /></figure>



<p>Because it’s such an issue, major efforts have been taken to keep it in check, and there’s been a widespread crackdown on buying email lists.&nbsp;</p>



<p>For instance, <a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/blog/tabid/6307/bid/32892/why-purchasing-email-lists-is-always-a-bad-idea.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Corey Wainwright of HubSpot</a> talks about how some purchased email lists contain something called a honeypot, “which is a planted email address that, when harvested and emailed, identifies the sender as a spammer. Similarly, things called spam traps can be created to identify spammy activity; they’re set up when an email address yields a hard bounce because it’s old or no longer valid, but still receives consistent traffic.”</p>



<p>So, if you use a non-permission-based email technique like buying a list, you run a far greater risk of lowering your sender score, which in turn, can lower your <a href="https://sleeknote.com/blog/email-deliverability">deliverability rate</a>.&nbsp;</p>



<p>But keeping things on the up-and-up and only sending email to readers who have given their consent has the opposite effect and should improve your sender score.&nbsp;</p>



<p>This means that a higher percentage of your emails will ultimately reach their intended inbox.&nbsp;</p>



<h2 id="5"><strong>Strong Brand Reputation</strong></h2>



<p>And think of the long-term impact on your brand reputation. Annoying the pants off of people with unsolicited email is a surefire way to create friction and ill will.</p>



<p>But keeping things above board where you get permission means people are not only more receptive to your brand but more likely to become loyal customers and in some cases brand ambassadors.</p>



<p>This can lead to further engagement, more referrals, and less churn over time.&nbsp;</p>



<h2><strong>Larger ROI</strong></h2>



<p>Finally, your money goes further with permission-based email marketing, with these campaigns having an average ROI of <a href="https://www.lyfemarketing.com/blog/permission-based-email-marketing/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">$38–$44 for every $1 spent</a>. </p>



<p>I couldn’t find any hard data on the average ROI of non-permission-based emails, but it’s safe to say that it would be significantly lower than this, as the open rate and click-through rate are microscopic.&nbsp;</p>



<p>So, if you’re looking to get the most bang for your buck, getting consent before emailing is a no-brainer.&nbsp;</p>



<h2 id="7"><strong>Examples of Brands That Have Completely Nailed Permission-Based Emails Marketing</strong></h2>



<p>The key to succeeding with this strategy is to:</p>



<ol><li>Be crystal clear that leads will receive promotional content by giving you their email address; and&nbsp;</li><li>Create an offer that motivates people enough to do so.&nbsp;</li></ol>



<p>Here are some of the best examples I’ve come across from brands that have completely nailed it and have built rock-solid email lists of leads that are totally dialed in.&nbsp;</p>



<h2><strong>1. Oribe</strong></h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="1024" height="504" src="http://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image6-3-1024x504.png" alt="Permission-Based Email Marketing" class="wp-image-115912" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image6-3-1024x504.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image6-3-300x148.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image6-3-768x378.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image6-3-1536x756.png 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image6-3-380x187.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image6-3-600x296.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image6-3-760x374.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image6-3-1440x709.png 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image6-3-71x35.png 71w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image6-3-102x50.png 102w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image6-3-740x364.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image6-3-220x108.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image6-3-385x190.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image6-3.png 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p><a href="https://www.oribe.com/oribestorefront/oribe/en/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Oribe</a> is an award-winning haircare brand that sells products for “the hair-obsessed.”</p>



<p>I love their opt-in for three main reasons.&nbsp;</p>



<ol><li>It’s ridiculously simple, with a beautiful minimalist aesthetic</li><li>It’s ultra-transparent</li><li>It succinctly highlights the benefits of signing up</li></ol>



<p>At a glance, Oribe’s shoppers can figure out that it’s an opt-in form, and that by signing up, they’ll receive targeted emails in their inbox. It’s cut and dry, and there’s no wasted cognitive exertion.</p>



<p>And by specifically saying that subscribers gain access to new releases and promotions, Oribe makes signing up much more attractive.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="1024" height="504" src="http://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image3-2-1024x504.png" alt="Permission-Based Email Marketing" class="wp-image-115909" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image3-2-1024x504.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image3-2-300x148.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image3-2-768x378.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image3-2-1536x756.png 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image3-2-380x187.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image3-2-600x295.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image3-2-760x374.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image3-2-1440x708.png 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image3-2-71x35.png 71w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image3-2-102x50.png 102w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image3-2-740x364.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image3-2-220x108.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image3-2-385x189.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image3-2.png 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<h2><strong>2. American Giant</strong></h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="1024" height="502" src="http://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image15-3-1024x502.png" alt="Permission-Based Email Marketing" class="wp-image-115921" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image15-3-1024x502.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image15-3-300x147.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image15-3-768x376.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image15-3-1536x753.png 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image15-3-380x186.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image15-3-600x294.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image15-3-760x372.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image15-3-1440x706.png 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image15-3-71x35.png 71w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image15-3-102x50.png 102w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image15-3-740x363.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image15-3-220x108.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image15-3-385x189.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image15-3.png 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>This is an American made clothing and activewear brand that uses simple, local, high-quality materials to create amazing products with workmanship their customers rave about.&nbsp;</p>



<p>When it comes to permission-based email marketing, <a href="https://www.american-giant.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">American Giant</a> has got it on lock. It utilizes a classic <a href="https://sleeknote.com/popup-examples">popup</a> that gets their shoppers’ attention without creating disruptions. </p>



<p>It’s extremely straightforward where they immediately ask shoppers to sign up for their email list, which is exactly the type of “not beating around the bush” approach you want to take with shoppers.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="1024" height="505" src="http://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image14-3-1024x505.png" alt="Permission-Based Email Marketing" class="wp-image-115920" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image14-3-1024x505.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image14-3-300x148.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image14-3-768x379.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image14-3-1536x757.png 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image14-3-380x187.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image14-3-600x296.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image14-3-760x375.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image14-3-1440x710.png 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image14-3-71x35.png 71w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image14-3-101x50.png 101w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image14-3-740x365.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image14-3-220x108.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image14-3-385x190.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image14-3.png 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>There shouldn’t be any guesswork to figure out what you’re asking them to do, and it should be totally transparent. And when it comes to incentives, offering shoppers who sign up 15 percen off their next purchase is a pretty sweet deal that many people are receptive to.&nbsp;</p>



<p>I also like how clear American Giant makes the offer, placing it in three different locations within the opt-in box—the headline, the copy, and the CTA.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="1024" height="507" src="http://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image20-3-1024x507.png" alt="Permission-Based Email Marketing" class="wp-image-115907" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image20-3-1024x507.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image20-3-300x149.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image20-3-768x380.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image20-3-1536x760.png 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image20-3-380x188.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image20-3-600x297.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image20-3-760x376.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image20-3-1440x713.png 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image20-3-71x35.png 71w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image20-3-101x50.png 101w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image20-3-740x366.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image20-3-220x109.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image20-3-385x191.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image20-3.png 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>That way they get things started out on the right foot with their shoppers, and zero subscribers will be caught off guard when they receive content from American Giant in their inbox.&nbsp;</p>



<h2><strong>3. NueBar</strong></h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="1024" height="504" src="http://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image4-3-1024x504.png" alt="Permission-Based Email Marketing" class="wp-image-115910" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image4-3-1024x504.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image4-3-300x148.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image4-3-768x378.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image4-3-1536x756.png 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image4-3-380x187.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image4-3-600x296.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image4-3-760x374.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image4-3-1440x709.png 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image4-3-71x35.png 71w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image4-3-102x50.png 102w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image4-3-740x364.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image4-3-220x108.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image4-3-385x190.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image4-3.png 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p><a href="https://nuebar.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">NueBar</a> sells “plastic packaging free, pH balanced, shampoo, conditioner, and face and body bars.”</p>



<p>Browse their website and social media accounts, and you can quickly tell they’re well branded and have built a strong rapport with their audience. And they’ve also done a great job of infusing permission into their email marketing campaign.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Notice how NueBar clearly tells shoppers what they’re asking them to do in their opt-in box.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The copy says, “Just by subscribing to our Nuesletter,” and the CTA says “Subscribe to our newsletter.”</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="1024" height="504" src="http://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image12-3-1024x504.png" alt="Permission-Based Email Marketing" class="wp-image-115918" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image12-3-1024x504.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image12-3-300x148.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image12-3-768x378.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image12-3-1536x756.png 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image12-3-380x187.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image12-3-600x295.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image12-3-760x374.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image12-3-1440x708.png 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image12-3-71x35.png 71w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image12-3-102x50.png 102w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image12-3-740x364.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image12-3-220x108.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image12-3-385x189.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image12-3.png 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>It doesn’t get much more transparent than that. As for providing shoppers with motivation to sign up, NueBar pulls that off brilliantly and offers two incentives.&nbsp;</p>



<p>First, shoppers will save 10 percent off their first order by subscribing.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="1024" height="506" src="http://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image16-3-1024x506.png" alt="Permission-Based Email Marketing" class="wp-image-115922" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image16-3-1024x506.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image16-3-300x148.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image16-3-768x379.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image16-3-1536x758.png 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image16-3-380x188.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image16-3-600x296.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image16-3-760x375.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image16-3-1440x711.png 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image16-3-71x35.png 71w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image16-3-101x50.png 101w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image16-3-740x365.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image16-3-220x109.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image16-3-385x190.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image16-3.png 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>Second, they’ll automatically be entered into a monthly drawing where the winner receives a NueBar bundle valued up to $90.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="1024" height="506" src="http://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image18-3-1024x506.png" alt="Permission-Based Email Marketing" class="wp-image-115924" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image18-3-1024x506.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image18-3-300x148.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image18-3-768x380.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image18-3-1536x759.png 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image18-3-380x188.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image18-3-600x297.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image18-3-760x376.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image18-3-1440x712.png 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image18-3-71x35.png 71w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image18-3-101x50.png 101w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image18-3-740x366.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image18-3-220x109.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image18-3-385x190.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image18-3.png 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>And if that wasn’t enough, NueBar lets shoppers know they’ll receive free shipping on orders over $60 in Australia.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="1024" height="504" src="http://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image2-3-1024x504.png" alt="Permission-Based Email Marketing" class="wp-image-115908" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image2-3-1024x504.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image2-3-300x148.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image2-3-768x378.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image2-3-1536x756.png 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image2-3-380x187.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image2-3-600x296.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image2-3-760x374.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image2-3-1440x709.png 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image2-3-71x35.png 71w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image2-3-102x50.png 102w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image2-3-740x364.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image2-3-220x108.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image2-3-385x190.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image2-3.png 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>They cover all of the bases here, and it should make for some extremely happy email subscribers who not only don’t mind receiving content but look forward to it.&nbsp;</p>



<h2><strong>4. Brooks</strong></h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="1024" height="501" src="http://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image1-2-1024x501.png" alt="Permission-Based Email Marketing" class="wp-image-115903" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image1-2-1024x501.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image1-2-300x147.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image1-2-768x376.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image1-2-1536x752.png 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image1-2-380x186.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image1-2-600x294.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image1-2-760x372.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image1-2-1440x705.png 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image1-2-72x35.png 72w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image1-2-102x50.png 102w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image1-2-740x362.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image1-2-220x108.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image1-2-385x188.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image1-2.png 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>Also known as <a href="https://www.brooksrunning.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Brooks Running</a>, this is a brand that specializes in top of the line running shoes and apparel. </p>



<p>While their opt-in box doesn’t explicitly state what will happen when a shopper enters their email address to the same degree as the other examples, I would wager that most shoppers can figure it out pretty easily.&nbsp;</p>



<p>I like the way that it starts out saying, “Let’s talk running,” which is a playful way to capture a visitor’s attention and get them to take notice.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="1024" height="498" src="http://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image10-3-1024x498.png" alt="Permission-Based Email Marketing" class="wp-image-115916" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image10-3-1024x498.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image10-3-300x146.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image10-3-768x373.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image10-3-1536x747.png 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image10-3-380x185.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image10-3-600x292.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image10-3-760x370.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image10-3-1440x700.png 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image10-3-72x35.png 72w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image10-3-103x50.png 103w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image10-3-740x360.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image10-3-220x107.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image10-3-385x187.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image10-3.png 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>Then, Brooks lists some of the benefits of signing up for their newsletter, including being the first to know about new gear, special collections, and other cool projects this brand is working on.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="1024" height="501" src="http://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image5-3-1024x501.png" alt="Permission-Based Email Marketing" class="wp-image-115911" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image5-3-1024x501.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image5-3-300x147.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image5-3-768x376.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image5-3-1536x752.png 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image5-3-380x186.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image5-3-600x294.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image5-3-760x372.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image5-3-1440x705.png 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image5-3-72x35.png 72w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image5-3-102x50.png 102w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image5-3-740x362.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image5-3-220x108.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image5-3-385x188.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image5-3.png 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>I also like that Brooks asks for a shopper’s gear preference, where they can choose female, male, or both.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="1024" height="498" src="http://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image9-3-1024x498.png" alt="Permission-Based Email Marketing" class="wp-image-115915" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image9-3-1024x498.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image9-3-300x146.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image9-3-768x373.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image9-3-1536x747.png 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image9-3-380x185.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image9-3-600x292.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image9-3-760x370.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image9-3-1440x700.png 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image9-3-72x35.png 72w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image9-3-103x50.png 103w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image9-3-740x360.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image9-3-220x107.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image9-3-385x187.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image9-3.png 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>This allows Brooks to send out super-targeted, uber relevant emails that hit their mark — something that’s incredibly important for keeping subscribers engaged and boosts click-throughs.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Add it all up, and this an awesome example of permission-based email marketing you can draw plenty of inspiration from.&nbsp;</p>



<h2><strong>5. East Fork</strong></h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img width="1024" height="505" src="http://sleeknote.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image17-3-1024x505.png" alt="Permission-Based Email Marketing" class="wp-image-115923" srcset="https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image17-3-1024x505.png 1024w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image17-3-300x148.png 300w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image17-3-768x379.png 768w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image17-3-1536x757.png 1536w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image17-3-380x187.png 380w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image17-3-600x296.png 600w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image17-3-760x375.png 760w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image17-3-1440x710.png 1440w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image17-3-71x35.png 71w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image17-3-101x50.png 101w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image17-3-740x365.png 740w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image17-3-220x108.png 220w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image17-3-385x190.png 385w, https://n7nqziuw1z4b1r6k2adhav10-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/image17-3.png 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>Lastly, here’s an Asheville, NC-based company that sells contemporary ceramic dinnerware made with materials that are regional to the Blue Ridge Mountains of Western North Carolina.</p>



<p><a href="https://eastfork.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">East Fork’s opt-in</a> is really simple and takes a unique approach where it features a testimonial from one of their satisfied customers that says, “East Fork truly knows how to put together a newsletter you want to read.”</p>



<p>Again, this doesn’t explicitly ask for permission, but it’s certainly implied with the combination of the testimonial saying it’s a newsletter you want to read combined with the “your email here” CTA.</p>



<p>That way shoppers know exactly what East Fork is asking them to do, and they won’t be surprised when they receive email content from this brand.&nbsp;</p>



<p>At the end of the day, permission-based email marketing is all about keeping it 100% transparent and giving shoppers a reason to sign up—both of which East Fork does in this example while taking up minimal real estate on their website.&nbsp;</p>


